ON manually.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Captured 42 metadata records and 42 transcript records for project\"\n}\n```\n\n## Codex Transcript Parsing\n\nPOC parser reads JSONL line by line.\n\nExpected Codex record types observed so far:\n\n```text\nsession_meta\nturn_context\nresponse_item\nevent_msg\ncompacted\n```\n\nObserved Codex shape is consistently top-level `{ timestamp, type, payload }`.\nUsefu\n[TRUNCATED]\necord-index` is the highest successfully parsed/captured source record\n  index; never advance it for a skipped partial final line.\n\nIf a transcript `cwd` exists, canonicalize it and accept it only when it is the\nrepo root or inside the repo worktree. Otherwise the POC should fail rather than\nguess. A future `--allow-cwd-mismatch` can relax this.\n\n## Deduplication\n\nUse stable record hashes from day one.\n\nStable record hash:\n| Agent auth/config/cache files | Never read |\n| Serialization/push | Not implemented in first POC |\n\n## Acceptance Tests\n\nMinimum tests before calling the POC done:\n\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog` passes.\n- Parses a Codex fixture JSONL with `session_meta`, `turn_context`,\n  `response_item`, and `event_msg`, and asserts extracted session id, cwd,\n  provider, model, and timestamps.\n- Missing transcript path fails clearly.\n- Unsupported agent fails clearly.\n- Default capture writes local metadata/cursors but does not write a transcript log.\n- Capture with `--include-transcript` appends envelope records to local-only\n  `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:<agent>:<session-key>:transcript`.\n- Metadata-only capture followed by `--include-transcript` still appends the\n  transcript envelopes once and keeps `seen-record-hashes` separate from\n  `transcript-record-hashes`.\n- Running capture twice on the same fixture reports `N` then `0` new records.\n- Record indexes are 0-based physical non-empty JSONL record indexes; empty lines\n  do not count, and skipped partial final lines do not advance the index.\n- Gro